r some political controversy, is facing demands to resign.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Such statements from people in charge should start with an apology in failing to protect citizens of Pakistan,\" Khadija Siddiqui, an activist and lawyer who was stabbed 23 times in an attack in 2016, told Al Jazeera.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"They should apologise that women in this country have to suffer every day,\" she said, adding that police officers who dealt with gender-based violence were often \"part of the problem\".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"They are complicit. Such people shouldn\'t be in these posts in the police sector where we expect them to be protectors of the state.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tahira Abdullah, a veteran human rights defender, was also angered by the incident.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"This is just the tip of the iceberg of violent crimes committed against women and girls which never get reported, especially in our rural [areas],\" said Abdullah.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, she said: \"It is a positive sign that this particularly heinous, barbaric gang rape and robbery case is receiving a lot of publicity, which just might lead to concrete action.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Pressing for drastic police reform on gender-based violence cases, Abdullah said there is a need for carefully designed training to inculcate the spirit of community-friendly policing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Each province needs a gender crimes unit staffed by specially trained women, along with hotlines, crisis shelters, immediate medico-legal aid, DNA testing, help in registering the case at the nearest police station, and longer-term PTSD trauma counselling and therapy.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Widespread condemnation&nbsp;</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Prime Minister Imran Khan\'s office said the protection of women was a priority for the government, adding that \"such brutality and bestiality cannot be allowed in any civilised society. Such incidents are a violation of our social values and a disgrace to society\".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Pakistan\'s human rights minister, Shireen Mazari, strongly criticised Shaikh for blaming the victim.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>According to the&nbsp;Punjab police, there have been at least 2,043 registered cases of rape and 111 cases of gang rape in the province this&nbsp;<a href=\"https://punjabpolice.gov.pk/crimestatistics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">year</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Harris Khalique, secretary-general of the independent Human Rights Commission of Pakistan (HRCP), said violence against women and children has increased over the last few years, during which HRCP has registered an average of 10 cases of gender-based violence a day, including sexual assault and the rape of minors.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"The gravity of the situation of the incident on the highway is the woman begging the police for the case not to be made public,\" said Khalique.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Stigma is attached to it and the victim is blamed.&nbsp; A woman is raped in front of her children, and the police chief of Lahore has the gall to say why she was driving late at night on her own.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Legal and policy measures need to be taken. The attitude change in society has to be brought, the increasing misogyny and intolerance of difference of opinion are all linked to each other,\" said Khalique.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '\'Heinous, barbaric\': Pakistan highway rape sparks outrage', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '849-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-09-14 07:39:26', '2020-09-13 21:39:26', '', 849, 'https://news.saras.care/849-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
